## Professional journey

I originally come from the French Alps where I worked for a few years before
having the opportunity to move to Berlin in 2015 to join
[Edenspiekermann](https://edenspiekermann.com). There, I learnt about building
digital products in an agile way and worked on a variety of projects, such as
Red Bull advertising and German and Swiss digital newspapers.

At the end of 2016, I joined [N26](https://n26.com) as a web tech lead
to hire a team and rebuild the N26 web platform from scratch. During my time
there, I focused on accessibility, security, documentation and team culture
building a diverse team of 25+ web engineers.

After 4 years at N26, I decided it was time for a change and joined
the quick-delivery startup [Gorillas](<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gorillas_(company)>) as one of
the very first engineers to build the Product & Engineering department. I spent 18 months
growing the organization, establishing practices and culture and leading web
engineering. I was unfortunately part of the wave of layoffs striking the
company in summer 2022.

This is how I got to join [cofenster](https://cofenster.com) as a VP of
Engineering at the end of 2022, making my move into the B2B world, changing
scale and pace in the process. I stayed there for 2 successful years until the
end of summer 2024. 

In October 2024, I joined Scilife as the VP of Engineering at [Scilife](https://scilife.io).
After a challenging yet successful transformation of the engineering organization, I decided
to look for something else for spring 2026.

For a more detailed version of my professional background, feel free to [read
my resume](/resume/) or [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/kitty-giraudel/).

